# Getting Support for AdvancedServerList

Please make sure to follow the below listed instructions to receive support with the plugin.

## Don't ask to ask, just ask!

Don't ask in chat if it is okay to ask a question or if anyone is around to help. Just state your question/issue and wait for a possible reply.

## Check that the plugin is up-to-date

Make sure the plugin is the latest available for your server/proxy version.
Up-to-date downloads can be found on [Modrinth](https://modrinth.com/plugin/advancedserverlist) and [HangarMC](https://hangar.papermc.io/Andre_601/AdvamcedServerList).

Supported versions are 1.20.6+ for Paper-based Servers and 1.20.x+ versions for Proxies.

## Explain your issue

Make sure to explain your issue **in detail**. If it helps to explain your issue, share screenshots.

## Share errors, logs and configuration files

Please share any errors you may get with the plugin alongside the `latest.log` of your server/proxy and optionally your configuration files used by the plugin.

**Do not share the files directly in chat or as a copy-paste!**

Use a pastebin service such as [pastes.dev](https://pastes.dev) for configuration files and smaller errors.
[mclo.gs](https://mclo.gs) is recommended for log files, as it hides sensitive information such as IPs.

## Check the Wiki

Always make sure you've checked the [AdvancedServerList Wiki](https://asl.andre601.ch) for any noteworthy information.

Recommended Pages:

- [Getting Started Guide](https://asl.andre601.ch/getting-started)
- [Profile options](https://asl.andre601.ch/profiles)
- [Commands](https://asl.andre601.ch/commands)
- [API Docs](https://asl.andre601.ch/api)

## Be patient!

The support for this plugin is provided "as is". No user, including the developer himself, is required to provide any support towards you and can choose to refuse it for any reason.
Any other user may also answer questions or help solve issues, meaning support may not be given by the dev himself.
